cs.GR, cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.CG, cs.AI. 

The paper deals with predicting clothing deformation in 3D as a function of human pose, shape, and garment style, which involves computer graphics (cs.GR) and computer vision (cs.CV) techniques. The paper also uses machine learning (cs.MM) and computational geometry (cs.CG) methods to develop the TailorNet model. Additionally, the paper discusses the physical constraints of garment deformation, which relates to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research.
